Ye reusability :- mtlb same code ko ham bar bar use kar sakte hai.

C++ me function ke 4 main parts hote hain:
Return type – ye batata hai function kya return karega (int, float, char, void, etc.)
Function name – function ka unique naam
Parameters / Arguments – input values jo function ko di jaati hain
Function body – curly braces {} ke andar ka code jo kaam karta hai.


Types:-
1. User-defined Functions
2. Standard Library Function

How to declare Function:-
return_type function_name(parameter1, parameter2....){
    statements;
}

1.Function name:_
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

int add(int a, int b) {   // here, 'add' is the function name
    return a + b;
}

int main() {
    int sum = add(5, 3);  // calling the function using its name
    cout << "Sum = " << sum;
    return 0;
}

....................................................
2.return type:-
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

int add(int a, int b) {   // return type is int
    return a + b;          // returns an integer
}

int main() {
    int sum = add(5, 3);
    cout << "Sum = " << sum;
    return 0;
}

........................................................
3.parameters:-
#include <iostream>
using namespace std;

int add(int a, int b) {  // 'a' and 'b' are parameters
    return a + b;
}

int main() {
    int sum = add(5, 3);  // 5 and 3 are arguments
    cout << "Sum = " << sum;
    return 0;
}


